OXPathParserVisitor
public class PAATEvalVisitor
extends OXPathVisitorGenericAdaptor<PAATStateEvalSet,OXPathType>

Class for evaluating OXPath queries over Abstract Syntax Trees. Used by the OXPathNavigator objects for query evaluation. Encodes the eval function of the PAAT Visitor (and calls eval_)

Author:
AndrewJSel

Method Detail

newInstance

public static PAATEvalVisitor newInstance(diadem.common.web.WebBrowser browser,
                                          org.slf4j.Logger iLogger,
                                          java.io.ObjectOutputStream os)
Call this method to instantiate a new PAATEvalVisitor instance to evaluate OXPath expressions. Implements the PAAT algorithm detailed in the OXPath VLDB '11 paper. While possible to evaluate multiple OXPath expressions with the same object, HIGHLY RECOMMEND using a new TreeWalker object for each expression evaluated through calls to this method, even if the browser, logger, and output stream are all reused.

Parameters:
browser - browser object to evaluate on OXPath
iLogger - the logging environment to pass messages to
os - the output stream to pipe away any OXPathExtractionNode instances
Returns:
a new PAATEvalVisitor instance for evaluating an OXPath expression

eval_

public OXPathType eval_(diadem.common.web.dom.DOMNode context,
                        Node astNode,
                        PAATStateEvalIterative state)
                 throws OXPathException
In order to trigger the proxy override via reflection (which doesn't happen with internal calls), this method is used whenever eval_ needs to be called (for either PAAT visitor).

Parameters:
context - the context node (this is redundant info - already encoded in state - but allows the proxy to cache the values in such a way that they can be cleared by page.
astNode - the node in the AST where we are at for evaluation
state - the EvalState at this point
Returns:
the output of eval_ at this point
Throws:
OXPathException - in case of exception
